data.chText: 致命的事故 / 一击 / 疾病

data.enText: a potentially fatal form of cancer

data.chText: 如果她再患病，就会有性命之忧。
data.enText: If she gets ill again it could prove fatal .

data.chText: 灾难性的；毁灭性的；导致失败的
任何延误都可能导致失败。
计划中有一个致命的缺陷。
data.enText: There was a fatal flaw in the plan.

data.chText: 现在要试图制止他们就会导致灾难性后果。
data.enText: It'd be fatal to try and stop them now.

data.chText: 这个计划一开始就有致命的缺陷。
data.enText: The plan was fatally flawed from the start.

ex.chText: 艾滋病是一种致命的疾病。

ex.enText: The nuclear bomb is one type of deadly weapons.

synonyms.bx: 指事物（如疾病、武器等）致命的。

ex.chText: 他设计的程序中有个致命的缺陷。
ex.enText: There was a fatal flaw in his program.

ex.chText: 那位年轻的候选人在大选中遭受了灾难性的打击。
ex.enText: That young candidate suffered a fatal blow in the election.

synonyms.bx: 强调死亡的不可避免性，多用于指疾病；还可指造成失败或毁灭性后果的。

ex.chText: 他在最后一次战斗中受到了致命的重伤。
ex.enText: He received a mortal wound in the final battle.
Our hotel is in mortal danger.

synonyms.bx: 主要指伤口等致命的，或情况非常危急的。

example: that fateful meeting of the U.N. when...it declared war on North Korea"- Saturday Re
the fatal day of the election finally arrived

tr: (of events) having extremely unfortunate or dire consequences
example: the stock market crashed on Black Friday
the battle was a disastrous end to a disastrous campaign
such doctrines, if true, would be absolutely fatal to my theory"- Charles Darwi
it is fatal to enter any war without the will to win it"- Douglas MacArthu

value.def: A fatal action has very undesirable effects.

example.ex: It would clearly be fatal for Europe to quarrel seriously with America...
example.tran: 欧洲若与美国反目显然会有致命的后果。

example.ex: He made the fatal mistake of compromising early...
example.tran: 他犯了过早妥协的致命错误。

example.ex: It would deal a fatal blow to his fading chances of success.
example.tran: 这将给他日渐渺茫的成功机会带来致命的一击。

value.tran: (行为)致命的，后果极严重的，毁灭性的

example.ex: Failure now could fatally damage his chances in the future.
example.tran: 现在失败会彻底毁掉他未来的机会。

value.def: A fatal accident or illness causes someone's death.

example.ex: ...the fatal stabbing of a police sergeant...
A hospital spokesman said she had suffered a fatal heart attack.
example.tran: 医院发言人说她死于心脏病发作。

example.ex: The dead soldier is reported to have been fatally wounded in the chest.
example.tran: 据报道，死去的那位士兵是胸部受了致命伤。
